    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. DENHAM:H.R. 4779.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8, of the United States Constitution,specifically Clause 1 (relating to providing for the commondefense and general welfare of the United States) and Clause18 (relating to the power to make all laws necessary andproper for carrying out the powers vested in Congress).[Page H5064]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Veterans Need Timely Access to Care Act - Directs the Secretary of Veterans Affairs (VA) to enter into contracts with such non-VA facilities as may be necessary to furnish hospital care or medical services to any veteran enrolled in the VA's patient enrollment system who: (1) has waited&nbsp;7 days or longer for an appointment for primary care, or 14 days or longer for an appointment for speciality care, in a VA facility; and (2) elects to receive such care in a non-VA facility.</p>]]></text>
